          </li>
          <li xml:id="PA_quotients5">
            <p>
              The convention we will follow is that the remainder will be the smallest positive integer <m>r</m> for which
              <m>-17 = 5q + r</m> and the quotient will be the corresponding value of <m>q</m>.
              Using this convention,
              what is the quotient and what is the remainder when <m>-17</m> is divided by 5?
            </p>
